      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HARTMAN (4) was in a different class last time with a dominant all-the-way win on the Devonport Synthetic over 1350m. Had won here three back and then didn't have the best of it as favourite at the track/trip after. He's likely to control the race from the inside barrier and can go on with the job. MAKE A DECISION (2) was doing his best work late, beaten a nose over 1220m at this track. He's busting to win and should manage the longer sprint this time around. The 1.5kh claim remains handy. HURRICANE KETUT (6) is third-up and should be ready to fire. Has been kept on the fresh side and rates right up to this at best. SISTER ROYAL (5) resumed for a new yard off four straight wins and needed the run here over 1400m. Keeps the leading rider, and quick improvement is likely.",
